WEBVTT

00:00.386 --> 00:01.548
Hear the word of the Lord.

00:03.931 --> 00:11.761
Now when John heard in prison about the deeds of the Christ, he sent word by his disciples and said to him, are you the one who is to come?

00:12.542 --> 00:13.643
Or shall we look for another?

00:14.725 --> 00:18.149
And Jesus answered them, go and tell John what you hear and see.

00:18.189 --> 00:28.082
The blind received their sight and the lame walk, lepers are cleansed and the deaf hear and the dead are raised up and the poor have good news preached to them.

00:29.250 --> 00:31.332
and blessed is the one who is not offended by me.

00:33.454 --> 00:36.878
As they went away, Jesus began to speak to the crowds concerning John.

00:38.320 --> 00:40.182
What did you go out into the wilderness to see?

00:41.183 --> 00:42.804
A reed shaken by the wind?

00:43.965 --> 00:45.367
What then did you go out to see?

00:45.387 --> 00:47.810
A man dressed in soft clothing?

00:48.951 --> 00:51.834
Behold, those who wear soft clothing are in King's houses.

00:52.755 --> 00:54.276
What then did you go out to see?

00:54.296 --> 00:55.858
A prophet.

00:56.386 --> 01:05.738
Yes, I tell you in more than a prophet, this is he of whom it is written, behold, I send my messenger before your face who will prepare your way before you.

01:06.940 --> 01:16.672
Truly, I say to you, among those born of women, there has arisen no one greater than John the Baptist, yet the one who is least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he.

01:17.674 --> 01:24.242
From the days of John the Baptist until now, the kingdom of heaven has suffered violence, and the violence take it by force.

01:25.122 --> 01:27.965
For all the prophets in the law prophesied until John.

01:28.286 --> 01:31.750
And if you are willing to accept it, he has Elijah who is to come.

01:32.391 --> 01:34.974
He who has ears to hear, let him hear.

01:36.676 --> 01:38.498
But to what shall I compare this generation?

01:39.359 --> 01:42.743
It is like children sitting in the marketplaces and calling to their playmates.

01:43.304 --> 01:45.466
We played the flute for you and you did not dance.

01:45.907 --> 01:47.809
We sang a dirge and you did not mourn.

01:48.170 --> 01:51.954
For John came neither eating nor drinking and they say he has a demon.

01:52.258 --> 02:03.031
The son of man came eating and drinking, and they say, look at him, a glutton, and a drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners, yet wisdom is justified by her deeds.

02:04.132 --> 02:11.021
The grass weathers and the flowers fade, but the word of our God will stand forever, and you may be seated, friends.

02:20.973 --> 02:22.034
Please join me in prayer.

02:26.530 --> 02:51.474
Blessed and merciful Father, as we now turn our attention to the preaching of your word, we ask that you would meet us here, that your spirit would be present, that you would take these words and make them alive, that you would do what no preacher can do and what no hero can do, that you would speak through your word this morning.

02:52.546 --> 02:55.852
All glory be to you, Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.

02:56.012 --> 02:58.175
One God now and forever.

02:59.437 --> 03:02.863
Amen.

03:02.883 --> 03:07.391
When I became a teacher, I expected to be asked a lot of questions.

03:08.613 --> 03:10.396
That's part of being a teacher.

03:12.239 --> 03:14.162
There's one question though that I was not

03:14.626 --> 03:16.128
expected that I would be asked.

03:16.188 --> 03:27.481
With anywhere near the regularity that I am asked it, at least once a semester in every single class I teach, one of my students raises their hand and says, Mr. Kemple, do you have a favorite student?

03:30.145 --> 03:31.386
I always answer it the same way.

03:31.406 --> 03:32.247
I'm sorry, Oliver.

03:32.287 --> 03:32.347
No.

03:32.447 --> 03:35.171
No, I don't have a favorite student.

03:36.733 --> 03:42.620
I do, however, have a favorite kind of student, a favorite type of student.

03:43.581 --> 03:44.562
See, I love

03:44.770 --> 03:47.494
teaching a student who doubts.

03:48.897 --> 03:57.089
I love teaching students who doubt, and if you've ever seen any movie where the main character is a teacher, you get what I'm talking about.

03:58.071 --> 04:05.022
I love teaching a student who's skeptical, who's paying close enough attention to things that they have to question what's going on.

04:07.406 --> 04:10.130
A student that says, Mr. Kemple, do you really care for me?

04:12.322 --> 04:16.487
Does Homer really in any way can communicate virtue that will make me a better person?

04:18.309 --> 04:21.012
Is this writing assignment really going to be beneficial?

04:23.095 --> 04:24.437
Does God really hear our prayers?

04:25.558 --> 04:28.021
Did Christ really come incarnate on earth?

04:28.602 --> 04:30.744
Is there even really a God up there at all?

04:32.186 --> 04:34.449
Are my thoughts worthy of attention?

04:35.870 --> 04:39.294
Do I have value apart from what I contribute and output?

04:41.297 --> 04:42.258
Students who doubt.

04:43.330 --> 04:47.915
is my favorite type of student to have in my class because they're engaged.

04:48.375 --> 04:50.398
They're bought in, they're asking questions.

04:52.420 --> 05:00.408
My guess is, though I don't know all of you, there are probably some of you here this morning who are wrestling with these same doubts.

05:03.131 --> 05:09.618
I met with a student recently and it started in a pretty typical way as far as meeting with students go.

05:10.562 --> 05:13.986
The student asked me the question, Mr. Kemple, how do I know if I'm a Christian or not?

05:14.747 --> 05:16.410
How can I know if I'm saved?

05:16.730 --> 05:21.036
And so we had a conversation and I gave them assurances and we talked about what scripture said.

05:21.757 --> 05:27.704
And then afterwards I asked them, what would make you feel comfortable that you were saved?

05:28.926 --> 05:34.193
What measure, what mark would you need to see in your life that would result in assurance?

05:35.695 --> 05:38.098
The student's answer was, if God spoke to me.

05:38.754 --> 05:46.505
If I heard him audibly say to me, you are a Christian, then I could rest sure that I believe.

05:48.147 --> 05:49.669
See friends, that's moved beyond doubt.

05:51.572 --> 05:53.795
Doubt says, I don't know what's real or not.

05:55.397 --> 06:04.530
We move beyond doubt to demand when we start to say, if you don't do this, God, then you are not really God.

06:05.432 --> 06:07.154
If you don't do this, then I,

06:07.330 --> 06:09.153
cannot and will not believe in you.

06:10.655 --> 06:13.139
That is exactly what we encounter in our text this morning.

06:13.960 --> 06:20.450
What we see in our text is that Jesus comforts those who doubt but confronts those who demand.

06:21.672 --> 06:27.340
Jesus comforts those who doubt but confronts those who demand.

06:28.382 --> 06:30.145
And we'll see this in two different movements.

06:30.886 --> 06:34.531
The first one, Jesus comforts those who doubt.

06:35.372 --> 06:36.434
The second one,

06:36.610 --> 06:38.853
Jesus confronts those who demand.

06:38.893 --> 06:43.399
Not very original this morning, I'm sorry, but hopefully it's easy to follow at least.

06:43.860 --> 06:51.189
We're gonna begin with our, with our first point, Jesus comforts those who doubt, but we do have sub points to this one.

06:51.230 --> 06:53.412
I'm sorry, I snuck in a third point really.

06:53.472 --> 06:57.958
So Jesus comforts those who doubt first by giving evidence.

06:58.740 --> 07:02.004
Jesus comforts those who doubt by giving evidence.

07:03.366 --> 07:06.610
Now when John heard in prison about the deeds of the Christ,

07:07.042 --> 07:15.434
He sent word by his disciples and said to him, are you the one who is to come or shall we look for another?

07:17.076 --> 07:25.668
If the pause here and unpack this, I know we're just getting started in the story, but we haven't been preaching Matthew up until this point.

07:25.728 --> 07:30.135
And so we need to have context for what's going on, like which John is this?

07:31.116 --> 07:32.718
What prison are we talking about?

07:34.120 --> 07:35.442
What do they mean look for another?

07:36.098 --> 07:38.381
So this John here is John the Baptist.

07:39.622 --> 07:53.780
Jesus' cousin, he's been arrested by Herod, and so he is now in a Jewish prison cell functionally, but really, really like a puppet type ruler for Rome.

07:55.562 --> 08:02.470
He was arrested because they didn't like the things that he was saying, especially the whole repent part because that means you're doing something wrong.

08:03.091 --> 08:05.554
So they arrested him, they've thrown him in jail,

08:06.722 --> 08:11.808
and he sends his disciples to Jesus and says, are you the Messiah?

08:13.330 --> 08:14.271
Should we keep on looking?

08:17.355 --> 08:21.700
Friends, this is an absolutely bizarre question to come from John the Baptist.

08:22.641 --> 08:23.942
Do you remember who John the Baptist is?

08:24.864 --> 08:30.290
He's the one that when he was still in utero and the Virgin Mary with Christ approached

08:30.370 --> 08:36.759
His mother Elizabeth, he left in her womb for joy because the Messiah approached him.

08:40.744 --> 08:57.366
He's the one who baptized the Christ, heard the Father declare from heaven, this is my beloved son in whom I am well pleased, saw the Holy Spirit descend as a dove, who upon seeing the Christ says, behold the Lamb of God who takes away the sins of the world.

08:59.149 --> 09:00.050
That's who John is.

09:03.394 --> 09:04.616
but he's wrestling with doubt.

09:05.617 --> 09:10.244
And we have to ask, why on earth is John wrestling with doubt?

09:10.344 --> 09:13.769
If this is who John is, how could he possibly have any doubt?

09:13.869 --> 09:15.090
What do you mean look for another?

09:17.414 --> 09:21.279
Well, it's because John is in a prison cell.

09:21.299 --> 09:31.954
And just like every other Jewish person living at that time, their understanding of the Messiah's coming was that he would violently overthrow the Roman oppressors

09:33.186 --> 09:39.873
And then they would rule with him as their king, replacing David, the mighty warrior, who's ruling over the nations.

09:41.615 --> 09:43.597
And boy, John's life does not look like that.

09:46.560 --> 09:50.003
Every time he wakes up, he's still in a prison cell.

09:52.325 --> 09:56.129
And in fact, he will not leave that prison cell.

09:56.490 --> 09:57.591
He will live nowhere else.

09:58.932 --> 10:00.914
He will be beheaded and die there.

10:05.090 --> 10:11.039
So as much as we like to sweep the idea of doubt away, we have to acknowledge this is reasonable.

10:11.900 --> 10:21.815
This is a reasonable question to be asking, and I have to ask you friends, where do you have doubt in your life because of unmet expectations?

10:25.060 --> 10:31.570
What conclusions did you come to life with or at this point in your life with saying, God's definitely going to do these things.

10:32.471 --> 10:34.354
He's going to give me this thing.

10:34.946 --> 10:37.409
Certainly, I'll have this from God.

10:39.311 --> 10:39.912
And now you don't.

10:42.475 --> 10:44.197
And so you doubt.

10:45.940 --> 10:47.602
It's perfectly reasonable.

10:48.142 --> 10:49.604
But do what John the Baptist did.

10:49.644 --> 10:51.166
Go to Jesus with those doubts.

10:51.206 --> 10:58.395
Don't let them harden to the point of demands and look and see how Jesus answers here as he gives evidence to John.

10:59.236 --> 11:04.082
And Jesus answered them, verse four, go and tell John what you hear and see.

11:04.322 --> 11:12.952
The blind receive their sight, and the lame walk, lepers are cleansed, and the deaf hear, and the dead are raised up, and the poor have good news preached to them.

11:13.632 --> 11:18.017
And blessed is the one who is not offended by me."

11:18.037 --> 11:20.780
This is a strange list in some ways.

11:22.022 --> 11:25.626
The beginning has all the things that you would expect for the coming of the Messiah.

11:25.986 --> 11:33.074
Deaf people are hearing, blind people are seeing, lame people are walking, lepers are being healed, the dead are raised to life,

11:33.794 --> 11:35.335
Of course, yes.

11:36.136 --> 11:40.500
And the government is overthrown and we are ruled by our good king forever and ever, right?

11:42.282 --> 11:43.263
It's not what Jesus says.

11:45.505 --> 11:52.872
In fact, the end of the list, what everything is building to, and the poor have good news preached to them.

11:55.995 --> 11:57.536
That's what this is all culminating in.

11:57.576 --> 12:03.442
The good news that Christ is declaring, to put it in English,

12:03.554 --> 12:06.136
the gospel, the good news.

12:07.398 --> 12:08.859
That's what this all culminates in.

12:09.320 --> 12:12.583
And then Jesus says something that's very reminiscent of the Beatitudes.

12:12.623 --> 12:16.987
And blessed is the one who is not offended by me.

12:18.028 --> 12:22.933
And don't think of offended in the way that we use that term politically now in our modern day.

12:23.333 --> 12:28.238
Think offended like the one who will not receive me, who will not take me in.

12:30.320 --> 12:32.722
Jesus is saying blessed is the one

12:34.050 --> 12:36.532
who doesn't reject me because of their expectations.

12:39.415 --> 12:50.165
Because I have an overthrown Rome, because I'm here to preach good news to the poor, blessed is the one who receives me, who is not offended by me, who does not reject me.

12:53.428 --> 13:00.515
John got an answer surprisingly, but it really shouldn't be that surprising, friends.

13:01.956 --> 13:03.858
This is what God does.

13:04.962 --> 13:18.296
When we go to God with genuine questions, genuine wrestling, we should not be surprised that God answers us, lovingly and mercifully answers us.

13:19.418 --> 13:26.185
I think so often we're afraid to admit doubts as if somehow us wrestling with doubts makes God less real.

13:28.127 --> 13:30.770
But friends, God is real enough that He can handle your doubts.

13:31.746 --> 13:34.990
So when you wrestle without go to God, pray to Him.

13:37.934 --> 13:41.999
Lord, I believe, help my unbelief.

13:43.160 --> 13:44.562
God honors those prayers, friends.

13:46.885 --> 13:49.248
But that's not the only way that He comforts John.

13:50.129 --> 13:56.477
He gives evidence, but also He gives honor, the second subpoint here, by giving honor.

13:56.577 --> 14:00.722
Jesus comforts those who doubt by giving honor in wherever seven.

14:02.370 --> 14:06.617
As they went away, Jesus began to speak to the crowds concerning John.

14:07.799 --> 14:09.521
What did you go out in the wilderness to see?

14:09.581 --> 14:11.985
A reed shaken by the wind?

14:13.007 --> 14:14.129
What then did you go out to see?

14:14.189 --> 14:15.651
A man dressed in soft clothing?

14:16.893 --> 14:19.878
Behold, those who wear soft clothing are in King's houses.

14:20.438 --> 14:22.041
What then did you go out to see?

14:22.061 --> 14:23.724
A prophet.

14:25.266 --> 14:26.308
Yes, and I tell you.

14:27.069 --> 14:30.354
Yes, I tell you and more than a prophet.

14:33.186 --> 14:37.091
See Jesus, I want you to picture this in your mind, not the Jesus part.

14:39.134 --> 14:40.576
So Westminster jokes, sorry.

14:41.137 --> 14:47.666
So you have a crowd of people who are there listening to Jesus instruct you or instruct them and teach them.

14:48.046 --> 14:57.719
And these people kind of push to the front to get where Jesus is, either followers of John the Baptist, and they ask him this question very publicly.

14:58.761 --> 15:02.706
Hey, John's wondering if you're actually the guy or should we keep on looking?

15:03.554 --> 15:04.575
So Jesus answers them.

15:05.056 --> 15:06.198
Tell John what you've seen.

15:06.538 --> 15:07.960
And then they go to do that.

15:07.980 --> 15:09.442
They leave to go tell John.

15:09.903 --> 15:23.601
And as they're walking away, certainly while they're still in earshot, Jesus addresses the crowd who has to be wondering who is there, some conflict between Jesus and John the Baptist now.

15:24.302 --> 15:29.148
Is there some discontinuity in this message that's declared?

15:32.693 --> 15:33.394
Some of you

15:33.858 --> 15:35.120
might remember from your childhood.

15:36.102 --> 15:37.845
Ooh, does mom disagree with that on this?

15:38.787 --> 15:39.028
Yeah?

15:40.490 --> 15:42.534
That's the type of thing that has to be going on there.

