John the Baptist did not know that he would be buried in three days later, raised from the grave, did not know that he would ascend into heaven, that he would pour out his Holy Spirit at Pentecost.

19:16.610 --> 19:18.432
John the Baptist couldn't have known those things.

19:19.454 --> 19:20.655
But friends, you do.

19:20.695 --> 19:36.256
And so because you have the greater revelation that God has given to us through His Word, through His Spirit, Jesus says, more blessed than John the Baptist is the least in the kingdom of heaven.

19:38.979 --> 19:41.102
And then we get to verse 12.

19:41.222 --> 19:44.146
I will read verse 12, I must confess,

