20:12.386 --> 20:14.689
these things will be translated a little differently.

20:15.070 --> 20:17.053
All of these have a slight different translation.

20:17.974 --> 20:18.815
Here's why.

20:19.116 --> 20:35.539
When it says the kingdom of heaven has suffered violence, that could mean one of two options, that the kingdom has actually suffered violence, which way the ESV translators take that, or that the kingdom has advanced violently.

20:38.824 --> 20:40.306
It's the same thing with the second part.

20:40.866 --> 20:56.100
And the violent take it by force, it could mean that violent people are seizing things or that through violence people are forcing their way into the kingdom or are being forced into the kingdom violently.

20:56.641 --> 20:59.463
So both of these clauses can be taken either way.

21:00.925 --> 21:02.827
My read on it for what it's worth.

21:02.927 --> 21:10.834
I think Dr. Dan Doryani has the best interpretation of this in that he says, yes.

21:11.170 --> 21:12.412
Both are true.

21:13.013 --> 21:30.840
Yes, the kingdom of God is being attacked with violence, and now violence is actually propelling it forward in a way that is upsetting all of the world till then, in a violent reordering of things, not through bloodshed, but through action and movement, the kingdom of God is advancing.

21:31.982 --> 21:36.789
And yes, violent people are forcing the kingdom of God ahead.

21:37.350 --> 21:40.114
They are taking things by force,

21:40.322 --> 21:45.692
but they are also those who were violent are being taken by the force of God.

21:46.594 --> 21:50.622
So I think it's a both and situation, especially as we continue here.

21:51.183 --> 21:55.752
He says verse 13, now, for all the prophets in the law prophesied and tell John.

21:56.253 --> 21:59.459
And if you are willing to accept it, he is Elijah who is to come.

22:00.300 --> 22:03.186
He who has ears to hear, let him hear.

22:03.682 --> 22:10.814
I think that verse 15 there is really the key to understanding that short passage there, that Jesus is speaking with a double meaning.

22:12.597 --> 22:15.322
And I think this is what we see throughout all of church history, right?

22:16.203 --> 22:19.108
The kingdom of God suffers violence and is propelled forward.

22:19.489 --> 22:26.520
The violent men who seek to harm the kingdom of God are actually brought into God's kingdom through their own hatred of their Messiah.

22:28.464 --> 22:29.906
I think of the Roman soldier

22:30.818 --> 22:36.325
who saw the crucifixion of Christ and churned and said, surely this man was the son of God.

22:39.009 --> 22:40.912
This is the way that God operates, friends.

22:42.294 --> 22:44.176
