Like you were brought into this thing.

23:17.178 --> 23:19.381
Again, this seems to be the way that God works.

23:20.482 --> 23:25.007
And Jesus continues to say that John is the Elijah who would come.

23:25.027 --> 23:28.370
This is from Malachi, the Elijah who would come before the Messiah.

23:29.954 --> 23:32.256
So Jesus gives John all of the honor.

23:32.817 --> 23:36.000
It says, look, John is the guy that you went to go see.

23:36.020 --> 23:36.601
That's who he was.

23:36.981 --> 23:38.202
He really was that prophet.

23:39.223 --> 23:50.435
And as John the Baptist's disciples are walking away, they hear this confirmation, and then Jesus turns on the crowd.

23:50.455 --> 23:57.362
And he goes from comforting those who doubt, to now confronting those who demand verse 11.

23:58.690 --> 24:05.279
Truly I say, sorry, verse 16, but to what shall I compare this generation?

24:06.340 --> 24:10.846
It is like children sitting in the marketplaces and calling to their playmates.

24:11.667 --> 24:13.790
We played the flute for you and you did not dance.

24:14.290 --> 24:16.613
We sang a dirge and you did not mourn.

24:20.218 --> 24:26.546
Almost every other time that Jesus talks about children in scripture, he does so in a positive light.

24:27.490 --> 24:30.313
He tells the disciples, and I'll keep the children from coming to him.

24:30.674 --> 24:37.422
He says that anyone who leads a child to sin and he better than a millstone was tied around their neck and they were thrown into a sea.

24:37.462 --> 24:45.071
He says that you have to become like a child to receive him, but not these children.

24:47.214 --> 24:54.322
These children are pouty, whiny, insistent, demanding cry babies.

24:54.818 --> 24:55.599
You know the type.

24:55.659 --> 24:57.861
You guys have all known kids like this.

24:59.623 --> 25:05.149
The type of kid who is losing the game so they pick up their ball and take it with them because they can't lose if the game's over.

25:08.173 --> 25:11.877
If you're really honest with yourself, you've all been kids like this.

25:15.881 --> 25:19.865
And if we're really truly honest, we've all been adults like this.

25:22.288 --> 25:24.210
My way or the highway.

25:26.242 --> 25:28.245
Do what I say or get out.

25:34.193 --> 25:43.326
The problem with this type of demanding, where it's different from doubt, is this demands control.

25:45.388 --> 25:48.813
If I do this thing, then you must do this in return.

25:52.739 --> 25:55.282
Friends, if this is how you have lived your life,

25:55.970 --> 26:03.020
controlling different situations and scenarios, people wielding this in an attempt to control God, to get what you desire.

26:03.080 --> 26:06.645
Friend, I plead with you.

26:07.726 --> 26:09.649
Turn away from this.

26:09.669 --> 26:10.129
Repent.

26:11.531 --> 26:12.392
It is heinous.

26:15.637 --> 26:25.330
It reminds me of a mentor and pastor that I once had who was convinced that God was leading him to leave this area and go plant a church, another

26:25.666 --> 26:27.188
city in the Pacific Northwest.

26:29.912 --> 26:42.411
And even though he was very good at his profession that he had outside of being a preacher and pastor, he couldn't find jobs anywhere in the large city that he was trying to move to.

26:43.853 --> 26:48.019
Even though their house was beautiful and reasonably priced, no one wanted to buy their house.

26:49.461 --> 26:55.410
And he became immediately apparent to everyone on the outside, God is not calling you.

26:55.586 --> 26:56.707
to go plant a church there.

27:00.231 --> 27:02.274
But he refused to listen to that.

27:02.894 --> 27:06.739
In fact, he said, God, you called me to do this thing.

27:06.759 --> 27:10.243
If I am not doing it, you must not be real.

27:10.263 --> 27:23.538
And so it brings me no joy to recount this, but he walked away from the faith through sins of alcoholism and illicit websites

27:23.842 --> 27:26.627
abandoned his wife and their children.

27:29.552 --> 27:32.618
This is what happens when we demand and play that we are God friends.

27:35.363 --> 27:37.086
We do not get to control reality.

27:37.226 --> 27:38.809
We cannot demand these things.

27:39.730 --> 27:43.537
This is what this generation he's talking to is like, and he gives a concrete example.

27:43.577 --> 27:48.466
For John came, verse 18, neither eating nor drinking, and they say he has a demon.

27:48.738 --> 27:55.546
The son of man came eating and drinking, and they say, look at him, a glutton and a drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners.

27:57.349 --> 27:59.151
Yet wisdom is justified by her deeds.

28:01.894 --> 28:06.980
John came not eating for a reason, and it was the wise decision to make.

28:07.641 --> 28:12.607
Jesus came eating and drinking for a reason, and it was the wise decision to make.

28:14.369 --> 28:15.290
That's how wisdom works.

28:15.891 --> 28:18.194
It's justified by its deeds.

28:18.530 --> 28:22.394
immediately readily apparent, which is the right thing to go.

28:22.454 --> 28:24.617
It takes wisdom to make that decision.

28:25.157 --> 28:26.539
That's what Jesus is talking about here.

28:27.520 --> 28:31.264
And so what are the deeds that wisdom wrought in both of these people's lives?

28:31.744 --> 28:38.252
In conclusion, when John the Baptist life, he prepared the way for Christ, the coming Messiah.

28:38.272 --> 28:38.812
That's what he did.

28:40.054 --> 28:41.095
Jesus just told us that.

28:42.216 --> 28:47.762
And friends, you know the result of the wisdom, the deeds that Christ committed.

28:48.482 --> 28:59.656
by drawing near to sinners, by approaching them, by eating with tax collectors, he showed that God welcomes those that the world despises.

29:01.699 --> 29:13.874
In living the perfect life and moving towards the outcast, Christ became identified with the outcast as he is nailed to the cross as our sins are nailed there with him.

29:16.386 --> 29:18.509
The beloved becomes the rejected.

29:21.654 --> 29:36.578
The source of all life dies, but three days later takes his life back up, ascends into heaven where he sits now at the Father's right hand, interceding for us.

29:40.164 --> 29:43.890
This is what the deeds of Christ accomplished.

29:44.450 --> 29:47.293
is what all of Israel was waiting for.

29:47.353 --> 29:52.298
And now we wait for His return.

29:53.480 --> 29:58.265
Looking forward, remembering that our God is a God who keeps His promises.

29:59.666 --> 30:04.672
Just as He did here, He will do eventually.

30:06.794 --> 30:10.838
And so we remember that when we have doubts, we take them to Christ.

30:11.099 --> 30:14.322
We run to Christ.

30:15.810 --> 30:18.254
We check our demands.

30:18.274 --> 30:31.597
We make sure that if we are someone who is struggling with taking control of these situations that we turn to God and ask Him to lead us to repentance, through a trust solely and entirely in Him.

30:34.342 --> 30:39.391
May we be a people who run to Christ with our doubts and who flee from our demands.

30:40.092 --> 30:41.234
Would you please pray with me?

30:44.674 --> 30:59.913
Merciful and gracious Father in heaven, Lord, we thank You that You sent Your Son to come and be with us, to move towards us.

31:01.015 --> 31:07.523
We thank You that You have sent Your Spirit to give us new life, that we could know You and believe in You.

31:08.424 --> 31:13.170
And we thank You for Your Word, and it always communicates the gospel to us.

31:14.722 --> 31:16.804
We pray all of these things in Jesus' name.

31:17.775 --> 31:18.098
Amen.

